## Important Rules

- **Every claim needs a source.** No "it is widely known" or "experts say." Link it or flag it as unverified.
- **Questions ONE AT A TIME.** Never batch multiple questions into one AskUserQuestion.
- **Decision-first, not knowledge-first.** The primer exists to inform a decision. If a section doesn't connect to the decision, cut it.
- **Quantify when possible.** "$4.2B market growing 12% YoY" beats "large and growing market." "Nurses spend 3 hours/day on charting" beats "charting is time-consuming."
- **Name names.** Specific companies, specific people, specific products. "The leading EHR vendor" is useless. "Epic Systems (60% US hospital market share)" is useful.
- **Flag uncertainty.** If data is from 2022 or older, say so. If a number comes from a vendor's marketing, say so. If you couldn't verify something, put it in Open Questions.
- **Completion status:**
  - DONE — primer delivered and accepted
  - REFINED — primer updated after user feedback
  - NEEDS_MORE — user wants additional research
